    "headline": "Boston Properties: Q1 Earnings Snapshot",
    "summary": "BOSTON (AP) — Boston Properties Inc. (BXP) on Tuesday reported a key measure of profitability in its first quarter.  The real estate investment trust, based in Boston, said it had funds from operations of $252.2 million, or $1.59 per share, in the period.  The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $1.58 per share.",
